SLS 26RS-380 ENGROSSED
2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 3
BY SENATOR MYERS
HEALTH CARE. Amends rules relative to criminal history background checks on licensed
ambulance personnel and nonlicensed persons.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To amend the Department of Public Safety and Corrections rule LAC 55:I.207(D) which
3 provides relative to criminal history background checks on licensed ambulance
4 personnel and nonlicensed persons; to direct the office of the state register to
5 incorporate the repeal into the Louisiana Administrative Code; and to provide for
6 related matters.
7 WHEREAS, LAC 55:I.207(D) requires licensed ambulance personnel and
8 nonlicensed persons to resubmit to the Bureau of Criminal Identification and Information
9 for a fingerprint background check when the result of a name-based background check
10 contains possible arrest information; and
11 WHEREAS, R.S. 49:969 provides that the legislature, by concurrent resolution, may
12 suspend, amend, or repeal any rule adopted by a state department, agency, board, or
13 commission.
14 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana hereby amends
15 LAC 55:I.207(D) adopted by the Department of Public Safety and Corrections, to provide
16 that implementation of LAC 55:I.207(D) is suspended until October 1, 2026.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
18 office of state register.
